PHEASANT RUN WIND, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Pheasant Run Wind, LLC ("Pheasant Run") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Pheasant Run generating facility ("Pheasant Run Facility").
Pheasant Run is a wind turbine generating facility located in Huron County, Michigan. The Pheasant Run Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by International Transmission Company, LLC and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Pheasant Run's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Pheasant Run Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Pheasant Run's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Pheasant Run shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $326,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $27,166.66.
